opinions on choke chains i was wondering what peoples opinions are on choke chain collars i see many people use them especially for labs are they for training or for dogs who tend to pull on the leash alot i don't use one nor do i need to but i was wondering what people thought about them and what their purpose was okay i can see why they would be good for training but i can also see why people dislike them oh i'm not going to use one i was just wondering about them i think a harness works much better when trying to control a dog excessive use of choke collars can irritate a dogs neck and trachea i don't think they're cruel to use for training purposes but i wouldn't recommend using them for every day use it puts a lot of strain on the dogs neck when it's pulled tightened Dog training Leash Chokehold Equine conformation Fox hunting Dog Professional wrestling match types Professional wrestling holds Urinary incontinence Bondage (BDSM) Carburetor Kitesurfing Labrador Retriever Horse tack Shotgun Social rule Humphrey Bogart The Marshall Mathers LP Pit bull Fecal incontinence Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban The Wonderful Wizard of Oz Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Working dog Laci Peterson Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Professional wrestling throws Tefillin Blood on the Tracks Steven Wright Horse Reservoir Dogs Stuttering Iditarod Weight training Basset Hound Dilbert Firefighter Keeshond Inspector Gadget Collar American Pit Bull Terrier Dogsled racing Cart Trapping Nunchaku Mixed martial arts Animal testing Obedience training The Shining (film) Mushing Garfield Tenshinhan Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Mercury 4 Working animal Abu Ghraib torture and prisoner abuse Originalism Manual transmission Screw Kodocha Command & Conquer: Red Alert 2 Dog agility Royal Victorian Order 7 July 2005 London bombings Theory of conduct Bulldog Syphon Filter Cat Internal ballistics Babe Ruth Rigging Hangman's knot Lung Time Out of Mind Cruising (ma